title: Lake Louisa Beginning Racer Program
description:
Join USA Level 1 Cycling Coaches Adam Baskin, Bob Tyler and Julie McKenzie as they lead the USA Cycling Beginner Racer Program (BRP) in Central Florida.

The USA Cycling BRP is designed to provide new racers an enjoyable and educational experience as they learn key skills to more safely race their bike. 

Registration is $20/session; for less than the cost of most races you will gain invaluable skills plus earn 2 upgrade points!

- Men 5 can earn an upgrade to Men 4 by attending all 5 sessions
- Men 4 can apply 3 of these points to Men 3 upgrade
- Women 4 can get halfway to Category 3 by attending all 5 sessions.

Attendees can attend any or all of the sessions, each beginning promptly at 5:30 p.m. Advance registration is recommended, day-of registration opens at 5:00 p.m. 

You will be taught the skill, participate in a mentored practice session, then be mentored in a 'practice race' with the skill as the focus. There will be a post-race 'debrief' to share feedback and answer questions.

Tues, 3/29 – “Protecting your Front Wheel”
Tues, 4/12 – “Cornering”
Tues, 4/19 – “Pack Awareness and Skills”
Tue, 5/3 – “Sprinting Basics”
Wed, 6/1: “Putting it all together” with the real Lake Louisa race being the mentored race.
course: State park with 10mi of roadways, varying from flat to rolling.  Minimal traffic in park on weekdays.
registration: Open to licensed and un-licensed cyclists of all abilities and experience levels.

title: 2016 UCI Supercross World Cup #5 - Sarasota, Florida
MCC of Tampa Bay Patriotic Ride

address.street: Davis Island Airport to MacDill Air Force Base and back

description: Patriotic ride for those who purchases an ALE MCC patriotic kit.  We will present a donation to the SOWF executive director on base.
course:
•	Ride begins on Davis Island at Davis Island Airport at 0830, ample parking is available on Davis Island
•	Riders will proceed down Bayshore blvd to Interbay blvd turning south on Dale Mabry to the main entrance of MacDill AFB. 
•	Enter MacDill AFB at the Dale Mabry gate at approximately 9:15
•	Ride route transits Hangar Loop Road – Golf Course Avenue – Bayshore Blvd to the Special Operations Memorial
•	MCC Tampa Bay conducts the presentation to SOWF Executive Director from 1000-10:15
•	Ride route exits MacDill AFB along Bayshore Blvd and out the Bayshore gate by approximately 10:30 or sooner.
•	Riders will return northbound on Bayshore blvd to Davis Island, taking West Davis blvd to the Airport parking lot.
registration: Registration is by invitation only for those that purchased an ALE MCC patriotic kit.
